33 SECTION 3.4. G.S. 58-56A-21 reads as rewritten:
34 "§ 58-56A-21. Claims data provided to health benefit plan.Duties owed to contracted
35 insurers.
36 (a) Fiduciary Duty. – A pharmacy benefits manager has a fiduciary duty to act in good
37 faith and fair dealing in the performance of all of its contractual duties, including all of the
38 following:
39 (1) Controlling costs.
40 (2) Acting in the best interest of the insurers and health benefit plans offered by
41 the insurers with which the pharmacy benefits manager has a contract.
42 (3) Acting with prudence and passing through any rebates or discounts the
43 pharmacy benefits manager received related to covered benefits bought and
44 paid for with the contracted insurer's assets or funds.
45 (4) Avoiding self-dealing and conflicts of interest.
46 (b) Claims Data Requests. – Upon the request of an insurer offering a health benefit plan
47 that contracts with a pharmacy benefits manager, the pharmacy benefits manager shall provide
48 the insurer with claims data that reflects the total amount the insurer paid to the pharmacy benefits
49 manager under the health benefit plan for a specified outpatient prescription drug, including the
50 ingredient cost and the dispensing fee. The pharmacy benefits manager shall also provide the
