41 adding a new section to read:
42 "§ 90-85.21E. Independent pharmacy prescriptions.
43 (a) An independent pharmacy may decline to fill or refill a prescription if (i) that act
44 would directly result in an unbearable cost to the independent pharmacy or (ii) the pharmacy or
45 pharmacist will be or is paid less than the acquisition cost for the covered drug, device, or service,
46 provided that the independent pharmacy meets the requirements of subsection (b) of this section.
47 If the independent pharmacy cannot find a pharmacy to accept the referral without causing harm
48 to the patient, then the independent pharmacy must fill the prescription. A pharmacy or
49 pharmacist declining to fill a prescription under this section shall not be a violation of any
50 provision of G.S. 90-85.40.
