24 PART VII. PHARMACY BENEFITS MANAGER AFFILIATES
25 SECTION 7.1. G.S. 58-56A-20 reads as rewritten:
26 "§ 58-56A-20. Pharmacy benefits manager affiliate disclosure; sharing of data.affiliates.
27 (a) A pharmacy benefits manager shall not, in any way that is prohibited by the Health
28 Insurance Portability and Accountability Act of 1996 (HIPAA), transfer or share records relative
29 to prescription information containing patient-identifiable and prescriber-identifiable data to a
30 pharmacy benefits manager affiliate.
31 (b) A pharmacy benefits manager shall not reimburse a pharmacy or pharmacist in this
32 State an amount less than the amount that the pharmacy benefits manager reimburses a pharmacy
33 benefits manager affiliate for providing the same pharmacist services or same prescription drug.
34 In determining the amount of the reimbursement for the purposes of this section, the amount shall
35 be calculated on a per-unit basis using the same generic product identifier or generic code number
36 and shall reflect all drug manufacturer's rebates, all direct and indirect administrative fees, and
37 any other cost-savings or discounts that may be given related to the drug or services. A violation
38 of this subsection is an unfair trade practice under Article 63 of this Chapter and under
39 G.S. 75-1.1 and is subject to all of the enforcement and penalty provisions of an unfair trade
40 practice under this Chapter and under Article 1 of Chapter 75 of the General Statutes."
41 SECTION 7.2. This Part becomes effective October 1, 2025, and applies to
42 pharmacist services or prescription drugs dispensed on or after that date.
