45 FOR PRESCRIPTION DRUGS
46 SECTION 8.1. Article 3 of Chapter 58 of the General Statutes is amended by adding
47 a new section to read:
48 "§ 58-3-182. Consumer protections/prescription cost-sharing.
49 (a) Definitions. – The following definitions apply in this section:
Page 16 Senate Bill 479-Fourth Edition

General Assembly Of North Carolina Session 2025
1 (1) Defined cost-sharing. – A deductible payment or coinsurance amount imposed
2 on an insured for a prescription drug that is covered under the insured's health
3 benefit plan.
4 (2) Reserved for future codification purposes.
5 (3) Reserved for future codification purposes.
6 (4) Rebate. – A formulary discount or price concession attributable to the
7 utilization of prescription drugs in the State and that is paid by a manufacturer
8 to a pharmacy benefits manager.
9 (b) When calculating an insured's defined cost-sharing for a covered prescription drug at
10 the point of sale, an insurer offering a health benefit plan shall base the calculation on the price
11 of the prescription drug after taking into account all rebates associated with that prescription
12 drug. The price of the prescription drug shall be reduced by an amount equal to ninety percent
13 (90%) of all rebates received, or to be received, in conjunction with the dispensing or
14 administration of the prescription drug.
15 (c) Nothing in this section shall preclude an insurer from decreasing an insured's defined
16 cost-sharing by an amount greater than that required under this section.
17 (d) By January 1 of each year, each insurer offering a health benefit plan shall submit to
18 the Commissioner a certification attesting that, for all health benefit plans offered in this State by
19 the insurer, the insurer has complied with the requirements of this section. The Commissioner
20 shall establish the form to be utilized for this certification.
21 (e) Failure to complete the certification or comply with any of the other requirements
22 under this section is a violation subject to G.S. 58-2-70. Each day that an insurer fails to complete
23 the certification is considered a separate violation.
24 (f) A violation of this section is an unfair trade practice under Article 63 of this Chapter
25 and under G.S. 75-1.1 and is subject to all of the enforcement and penalty provisions of an unfair
26 trade practice under this Chapter and under Article 1 of Chapter 75 of the General Statutes."
27 SECTION 8.2. G.S. 58-56A-3 is amended by adding a new subsection to read:
28 "(c3) G.S. 58-3-182 applies to pharmacy benefits managers when calculating an insured's
29 out-of-pocket cost for a covered prescription drug."
30 SECTION 8.3. This Part is effective October 1, 2025, and applies to prescription
31 drugs purchased on or after that date.
